description:
Wild Bill Hickok's Gunfight at Hayes City

Just the mention of the name "Wild Bill Hickok" was enough to bring expressions of awe to the faces of even the most hardened in the days of the roaring West. To the lawabiding it meant comfort and security... to the lawless: fight or death. While marshal of Hayes City "Wild Bill" had several adventures that enhanced his already fabulous reputation.

Annie Oakley Queen of the Sharpshooters

Annie Oakely was known throughout the world for her almost unbelievable accuracy with a rifle. As a result, her life was full of unusual and breathtaking adventures... one of which occurred while she was on tour in Germany with Buffalo Bill and his Wild West Show...

The Double Justice

Justice wasn't too plentiful in the days of the old West but a man was usually hung for murder, if he could be caught... ...but read about the man who everybody thought got away with murder!

Jesse James The Great Train Robbery

Jesse James, one of the most fabulous and most ingenius of the West's bandits, invented with his ruthless, rip roaring band the altogether new and profitable art of... train robbing... it was so new, in fact, even he couldn't figure all the angles

Green Hornet and Kato's confrontation with The Black Hornet has left them in an unimaginable death trap of epic proportions. Only Kato's drastic, dangerous gambit can save them. Even if it does, The Black Hornet's insidious plans for Century City spell doom for our heroes. Only their self sacrifice can prevent the utter destruction of their beloved city. Will the new Green Hornet's first mission also be his last?
